ller of the Great State of Pennsylvania has been an outstanding State Rep. Now he is running as the Republican Nominee for Congress, and has my Complete and Total Endorsement. Strong on Crime, Second Amendment, Military, Vets, and Healthcare. He will do a fantastic job!|work=Twitter|author=Donald J. Trump}}</ref>\n* [[Tom Marino]], former U.S. Representative (PA-12)<ref name=Klands>{{cite news |url=http://www.sungazette.com/news/top-news/2019/03/keller-lands-republican-nomination/ |title=Keller lands GOP nomination |date=March 2, 2019 |first=Derek |last=Danneker |newspaper=Williamsport Sun-Gazette |access-date=March 29, 2019 }}</ref>\n* [[Glenn Thompson (politician)|G.T. Thompson]], U.S. Representative (PA-15)<ref name=Klands />\n* [[Guy Reschenthaler]], U.S. Representative (PA-14)<ref>{{cite web|author=Guy Reschenthaler |url=https://twitter.com/reschenthaler/status/1102222464120209408 |title=Congrats to @VoteFredKeller for winning the #PA12 Republican Nomination! I am looking forward to serving with you in Congress. |publisher=Twitter.com |date=2019-03-03 |accessdate=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n* [[Lou Barletta]], former U.S. Representative (PA-11) and Republican nominee for U.S. Senate in [[2018 United States Senate election in Pennsylvania|2018]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Fred Keller |url=https://twitter.com/VoteFredKeller/status/1118948661793308672 |title=Grateful for @RepLouBarletta's service to our community and for his help and support in my campaign for Congress. One of the all time good guys! |publisher=Twitter.com |date=2019-04-18 |accessdate=2019-07-15}}</ref>\n\n; Local officeholders\n* Joe Kantz, Snyder County Commissioner Chairman<ref name=\"rlrse4\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fredkellerforcongress.com/news/2019/2/21/snyder-county-commissioner-chair-kantz-sheriff-zechman-recommend-keller|title=Snyder County Commissioner Chair Kantz, Sheriff Zechman Recommend Keller|work=Fred Keller for Congress|date=February 21, 2019}}</ref>\n* John Zechman, Snyder County Sheriff<